init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Any level-headed reading of recent news will surely convince you things are hopeless.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So, why read news at all?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you don't know what's going on, things can, well, catch you by surprise.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: How can you be informed without being hopeless?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: How can you carry a literate conversation without making yourself miserable?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: develop a short list of facts, orient it around your values, and read it daily.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: orient it around your values, and read it daily.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: That's how most people sound intelligent at parties after all.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So why not hit the retirement years worry free  or as worry free as possible anyway.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you choose that route remember: always answer in the affirmative, it is the path of least resistance.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's much easier to say "yes" than to offer a dissenting opinion.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You will come off as worldly, intelligent, and in control of your own destiny.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And if you really want to hear yourself talk, consider running for office.
